There are 3 main categies of design patters. Creational to create objects in a controlled way, Structural to provide new functionality to the class structures, Beahvioral to provide common communcation patterns between objects.
* Creational patters examples:
  - Factory method
  - Singleton
  - Builder
 - ...
* Structural pattern examples:
  - Adapter/ Wrapper
  - Composite
  - Facde
  - Proxy
  - ...
* Behavioural pattern examples:
  - Command
  - Iterator
  - Observer
  - Strategy
  - Template method

references
[1] https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Software_design_pattern
